[The new cases indicate that there may still be an increased risk of
falciparum malaria transmission in and around Goa, in India. There have
been no reports from the Indian authorities of increased malaria
transmission in the local population, although such infection is likely, as
travellers are exposed for a very short time in Goa and have become
infected. A number of European countries are recommending increased
personal protection and optional malaria chemoprophylaxis for travellers to
and around Goa. This latest case suggests that this recommendation be
maintained until further evidence from India suggests it is no longer
necessary. - Mod.EP
A map of India is available at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_pol01.jpg>. -
CopyEd.MJ]
